document.title: Alpha Aloha Fund Market and Fund Update Report - Feb 6, 2025
document.description: Detailed performance insights for the Alpha Aloha Fund, including NAV, cash position, earnings strategy, and macroeconomic trends.

body.raw:
# Alpha Aloha Fund Market and Fund Update Report

**Reporting Period:** February 6, 2025

## NAV & Cash Position
- **NAV (Maintenance Capital at Risk):** $7,678,000
- **Cash Position:** $5,653,000

---

## Performance Overview
**Daily Performance (Feb 6, 2025):**
- Net Income (Day): $16,928.45 (0.22% of NAV)
- Proceeds: $1,514,209.76 | Cost Basis: $1,522,770.83
- Gain/Loss Ratio: 100% | Win Rate: 100%

**Month-to-Date Performance (Feb 2025):**
- Net Income: $134,366.45 (1.75% of NAV)
- Proceeds: $3,028,419.52 | Cost Basis: $3,045,541.66

---

## Strategy Highlights
- Amazon (AMZN) Earnings Play: Sold the wall on AMZN to capture IV volatility.
- Rolling Over High RSI Positions: Managed JPM holdings efficiently.

---

## Market Commentary
**Tech Sector Resilience:**
- Amazon (AMZN) reported strong earnings but provided lighter Q1 guidance.
- Alphabet (GOOGL) shares dipped due to increased CapEx plans.

**Macro Insights:**
- Dow +0.71%, Nasdaq +1.64%, signaling investor optimism.

---

## Closing Remarks
The Alpha Aloha Fund maintains disciplined strategies in premium capture, risk management, and sector rotation. With a NAV of $7.678 million and a strong cash position of $5.653 million, we continue leveraging opportunities for alpha generation.

**Onward to new heights!** ðŸ™Œ

document.title: Hushh Technologies Alpha Fund, LP â€“ Fee Schedule
document.description: Detailed breakdown of management and performance-based fees for Limited Partners.

body.raw:
# Hushh Technologies Alpha Fund, LP â€“ Fee Schedule

**Effective Date:** February 3, 2025

---

## 1. Management & Performance Fee Structure
The Fund charges a management fee for operational expenses and a performance fee based on net new profits. Fees vary by LP Class.

---

## 1.1 Summary of Fees by Class
- **Class A (Institutional LPs):** Minimum Investment: $25M | Management Fee: 1.50% | Performance Fee: 20%
- **Class B (HNW & Family Offices):** Minimum Investment: $5M | Management Fee: 1.75% | Performance Fee: 22.5%
- **Class C (Accredited LPs):** Minimum Investment: $1M | Management Fee: 2.00% | Performance Fee: 25%

---

## 2. Fee Breakdown & Calculation Methodology
- **Management Fee:** Charged quarterly based on AUM.
- **Performance Fee:** Applied annually, only on new profits above the high-water mark.

---

## 3. Additional Fees & Expense Allocations
- **Trading & Execution Costs:** Competitive brokerage rates applied.
- **Legal & Compliance Costs:** SEC, CFTC, and state-level compliance expenses prorated across LPs.
- **Technology & AI Infrastructure:** Costs covered by management fees.

---

## 4. Redemption & Early Exit Fees
- **Class A:** No redemption fees (subject to lock-up period).
- **Class B & C:** Redemptions above 20% of NAV per quarter may incur a 1.0% liquidity surcharge.
- **Early Exit Fees:**
  - Class A: 1.5% penalty.
  - Class B: 2.0% penalty.
  - Class C: 3.0% penalty.

---

## 5. Summary
The Hushh Technologies Alpha Fund employs a transparent fee structure focused on long-term value creation and investor alignment.

body.raw:
# Hushh Alpha Fund â€“ NAV Update & Earnings Report (As of January 31, 2025)

**Published At:** 2025-01-31  
**Description:** Comprehensive NAV update and earnings report for Hushh Alpha Fund, highlighting key performance metrics and strategic insights.  
**Category:** Fund Updates  

## ðŸ“… Reporting Period: December 30, 2024 â€“ January 31, 2025

**ðŸ’° Fund Strategy:** Systematic Cash Flow Generation via â€˜Sell the Wallâ€™ on Top 10 Free Cash Flow Businesses  
**ðŸ“Š Risk Profile:** Max Drawdown SPX Â±15%, Targeted Weekly Returns 1.5-2.0% of AUM  

## ðŸ“Œ Key Highlights for January 2025
1. 1ï¸âƒ£ Best Month in Fund History â€“ $725,150 in net income
2. 2ï¸âƒ£ Hit High-Water Mark â€“ NAV crossed $7.5M, setting new capital efficiency benchmarks.
3. 3ï¸âƒ£ 100% Weekly Win Rate â€“ Every trading week in January was profitable.
4. 4ï¸âƒ£ SPX Market Volatility Captured Effectively â€“ IV Crush and Earnings Volatility resulted in maximum premium decay collection.
5. 5ï¸âƒ£ Key Earnings Plays: Apple (AAPL), Microsoft (MSFT), Tesla (TSLA), Meta (META), NVIDIA (NVDA)
6. 6ï¸âƒ£ Capital Deployment Remains Highly Efficient â€“ Less than 50% margin utilization at peak while generating consistent returns.

---

## ðŸ“Š Fund Performance Summary

### ðŸ“… Monthly (Jan 2025)
- **Total Proceeds:** $9,725,480.00
- **Total Cost Basis:** $9,000,330.00
- **Net Gain:** $725,150.00 (+8.06%)
- **Gain Ratio:** 67.3%
- **Annualized IRR (Based on January Run Rate):** 96.72%
- **Max Drawdown:** -2.8% (During NVDAâ€™s 3-day pullback)

### ðŸ“… Weekly (Jan 27 - Jan 31, 2025)
- **Total Weekly Proceeds:** $1,795,830.00
- **Weekly Net Gain:** $150,734.00 (+2.00%)
- **Gain Count:** 247
- **Loss Count:** 4
- **Weekly Gain Rate:** 98.4%
- **SPX Weekly Performance:** +1.7% (Fund Outperformed by 30bps)

---

## ðŸ“ˆ NAV Breakdown (As of Jan 31, 2025)
- **Total AUM (Net Asset Value):** $7,500,000.00
- **Margin Utilization:** 43.6% ($3.27M active at peak)
- **Cash Reserves & Hedging Capital:** $2.12M (Maintained for downside hedging)
- **Leverage Ratio:** 1.55x (Strictly within risk thresholds)

---

## ðŸ”Ž Portfolio Breakdown (Sell the Wall Strategy)
### âœ… Top 5 Cash Flow Machines (Primary Positions for January 2025)
- **AAPL:** 19.2% Allocation, $155,200 Options Premium Income, +6.5% P/L, $44,600 IV Collapse Gain
- **MSFT:** 17.5% Allocation, $135,700 Options Premium Income, +4.2% P/L, $33,750 IV Collapse Gain
- **NVDA:** 14.6% Allocation, $112,000 Options Premium Income, -2.5% P/L, $28,900 IV Collapse Gain
- **META:** 13.1% Allocation, $98,900 Options Premium Income, +8.9% P/L, $25,300 IV Collapse Gain
- **TSLA:** 10.4% Allocation, $85,300 Options Premium Income, +1.4% P/L, $19,650 IV Collapse Gain

### ðŸ’¡ Observation:
- ðŸ“Œ AAPL led the way â€“ Record earnings beat and continued free cash flow dominance.
- ðŸ“Œ NVDA provided key IV crush income despite minor stock pullback.
- ðŸ“Œ META capitalized on ad revenue strength, returning 8.9% equity gains.

---

## ðŸŽ¯ Strategy & Execution
### How We Captured Alpha This Month
- âœ… â€˜Sell the Wallâ€™ Covered Call & Put Laddering Strategy
  - ðŸ“Œ Sold calls deep out of the money (OTM) before earnings, collecting premium during IV spikes.
  - ðŸ“Œ Executed post-earnings IV collapse trades to close profitable positions early.
- âœ… Earnings Volatility Capture
  - ðŸ“Œ Focused heavily on earnings plays across AAPL, NVDA, META, MSFT, TSLA.
  - ðŸ“Œ Used pre-earnings straddle and post-earnings IV crush strategies.
- âœ… AI & ML-Based Risk Hedging
  - ðŸ“Œ Adaptive delta-neutral adjustments prevented excessive directional exposure.
  - ðŸ“Œ Maintained systematic hedging with rolling put spreads for downside protection.

---

## ðŸ“Š Market Commentary & Key Observations
- ðŸ”¥ January 2025 â€“ The Month of Resilient Tech
- ðŸ“Œ Apple Just Canâ€™t Stop Winning â€“ $69B iPhone revenue, $26.3B in Services. Wall Street traders are now convinced that people will buy iPhones even during the apocalypse.
- ðŸ“Œ Microsoftâ€™s AI Playbook Works â€“ 31% Azure growth, Copilot subscriptions skyrocket. Apparently, people love paying Microsoft even more for products they already bought.
- ðŸ“Œ Teslaâ€™s Rollercoaster Continues â€“ Musk hinted at next-gen AI-powered vehicles, but the real market mover? â€œFull Self-Drivingâ€ subscriptions ballooning. Turns out people are willing to pay extra to believe their car is thinking.
- ðŸ“Œ NVIDIA Sees a Speed Bump â€“ A short-term AI-chip demand pullback scared markets for about 48 hours before everyone remembered that Jensen Huang runs a global AI monopoly.
- ðŸ“Œ Metaâ€™s Advertising Machine is Back â€“ The $15B ad revenue print silenced all skeptics. Who knew selling ads next to baby pictures and conspiracy theories was this lucrative?

---

## ðŸ’¡ Next Steps & Execution Plan for February 2025
- **ðŸ“Œ Tactical Adjustments**
  - ðŸ”¹ More Active Sector Rotation â€“ Trimming exposure to high-volatility tech after record earnings.
  - ðŸ”¹ Expanding Sell the Wall Across More Dividend & FCF Giants â€“ Adding BRK/B, AVGO, LLY as new core holdings.
  - ðŸ”¹ Rebalancing Hedging Strategies â€“ Scaling into more protective long-term put strategies.
- **ðŸš€ Goals for February**
  - ðŸ“Œ Targeting another $750K in net income.
  - ðŸ“Œ Maintain strong liquidity and risk-adjusted alpha.
  - ðŸ“Œ Finalize next institutional capital raise to scale beyond $50M AUM.

---

## ðŸŽ¤ Closing Thoughts: The Future of Systematic Income
- ðŸ“Œ Tech mega caps continue to dominate cash flow & options markets.
- ðŸ“Œ â€˜Sell the Wallâ€™ strategy is proving to be a sustainable, scalable model for systematic alpha.
- ðŸ“Œ Hushh Fund is well-positioned to scale towards institutional-grade AUM targets.

**ðŸ’¡ As Charlie Munger once said:**  
"The big money is not in the buying and sellingâ€¦ but in the waiting. But if you can collect premium while waiting, youâ€™re playing the game on another level."

**ðŸ›  Next Report:** February 2025 Earnings Recap & Fund Performance Update ðŸš€

document.title: Fund A Hushh
document.description: An in-depth overview of Fund A Hushh, focusing on AI-driven, risk-managed investment strategies.

body.raw:
# Hushh Technologies Alpha Fund, LP â€“ Fee Schedule

**Effective Date:** February 5, 2025

---

## 1. Management & Performance Fee Structure
The Fund charges a management fee for operational expenses and a performance fee based on net new profits. Fees vary by LP Class.

---

## 1.1 Summary of Fees by Class
- **Class A (Institutional LPs):** Minimum Investment: $25M | Management Fee: 1.50% | Performance Fee: 20%
- **Class B (HNW & Family Offices):** Minimum Investment: $5M | Management Fee: 1.75% | Performance Fee: 22.5%
- **Class C (Accredited LPs):** Minimum Investment: $1M | Management Fee: 2.00% | Performance Fee: 25%

---

## 2. Fee Breakdown & Calculation Methodology
- **Management Fee:** Charged quarterly based on AUM.
- **Performance Fee:** Applied annually, only on new profits above the high-water mark.

---

## 3. Additional Fees & Expense Allocations
- **Trading & Execution Costs:** Competitive brokerage rates applied.
- **Legal & Compliance Costs:** SEC, CFTC, and state-level compliance expenses prorated across LPs.
- **Technology & AI Infrastructure:** Costs covered by management fees.

---

## 4. Redemption & Early Exit Fees
- **Class A:** No redemption fees (subject to lock-up period).
- **Class B & C:** Redemptions above 20% of NAV per quarter may incur a 1.0% liquidity surcharge.
- **Early Exit Fees:**
  - Class A: 1.5% penalty.
  - Class B: 2.0% penalty.
  - Class C: 3.0% penalty.

---

## 5. Summary
The Hushh Technologies Alpha Fund employs a transparent fee structure focused on long-term value creation and investor alignment.

body.raw:
# ðŸ¤« Fund Performance â€“ January 28, 2025

## Fund Updates â€“ January 28, 2025

**Fund performance update covering net liquidation value, transaction statistics, and strategic commentary.**

---

## ðŸ“Š Fund Overview
- **Net Liquidation Value:** $6,000,654.31
- **Proceeds:** $240,269.56
- **Net Gain:** +15.28%

---

## Transaction Statistics
- **Transaction Count:** 29
- **Gain Count:** 29
- **Loss Count:** 0
- **Gain/Loss Ratio:** 100% gain rate
- **Average Gain:** +15.28%

---

## Strategic Commentary
- **Sell the Wall Execution:** Maximized premium collection on AAPL and NVDA.
- **Balanced Strike Prices:** Tesla (TSLA) and Amazon (AMZN) optimized for gains.
- **Hedged Exposure:** Protective puts for META and TSLA.

---

## Outlook
- **Market Direction:** Strength in tech sectors expected.
- **Portfolio Adjustments:** Rolling positions into higher volatility weeks.
- **Focus Areas:** GOOGL, AAPL, and diversification with BRK.B.

---
